description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Secondment 6 months - Open to employees of NHS only &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting secondment opportunity for a therapist or nurse in our physical health services within the intermediate care tier (D2A) of CPFT, for a full time (37.5 hours per week) team lead in the Cambridge team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be at the forefront of facilitating a smooth seamless service between the discharging hospitals and the care at home services supporting the home first and discharge to assess models.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joint leading the multidisciplinary Intermediate Care team, you will need to offer clinical oversight and leadership to ensure the effective delivery of the intermediate care service with Cambridge city and the wider area, working alongside the current team lead. The post has been created due to increased volume of patients coming through the new pathway.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicant will need to be innovative, decisive and clinically astute to flex within the system to maximise resource and support the system, embed the discharge to assess pathway and reduce delayed transfers of care for medically optimised patients within the East of England, working collaboratively with our partner organisations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is open to those with either therapy or nursing background holding a HCPC registration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Barry Underwood&lt;/strong&gt; (Intermediate Care Ops Manager - South)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;barry.underwood@cpft.nhs.uk - 07983 343253&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nicki Brady&lt;/strong&gt; (Intermediate Care Ops Manager - North)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07967 773257&lt;/p&gt;
